Package: jst
Title: JSON Value Types via S7 Classes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides S7 classes for representing JSON value types (null,
    boolean, number, string, array, object).  Typed JSON values can be
    constructed with json_null(), json_boolean(), json_number(),
    json_string(), json_array(), and json_object(), and serialised to
    JSON text via format() / print().
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
